cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.HC, cs.AI, cs.MM

The paper proposes a deep learning framework for assessing neonatal pain from videos, which involves analyzing facial expressions and body movements. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category. Additionally, the use of deep learning models such as convolutional neural networks (CNN) and recurrent neural networks (LSTM) suggests that the paper may also belong to the machine learning (cs.LG) sub-category. The focus on assessing pain in neonates suggests that the paper may also belong to the human-computer interaction (cs.HC) sub-category. The use of deep learning models for analyzing facial expressions and body movements also suggests that the paper may belong to the artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-category. Finally, the use of videos as input data suggests that the paper may also belong to the multimedia (cs.MM) sub-category.
